SocialDynamicsOfScience

Interface ISDoS

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Author, Community, Discipline, Paper, SocialDynamicsOfScienceSimulator

    public interface ISDoS
    An interface for Social Dynamics of Science agents. It purpose to suffice type safety among agents of context. There are three elements in the SDS model: papers, authors, and disciplines. It represents a social network among authors. The social network starts with one author writing one paper in one discipline. The network then evolves as new authors join, new papers are written, and new disciplines emerge over time.
    Version:
    V1.0 - Alpha
    Author:
    Kemal Akkoyun $ 11076004
